  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Facilitation of Access to Healthcare and Material Support for the Refugees and Migrants in Greece</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">There are currently 64,900 refugees and migrants in Greece (based on those since the start of the crisis in 2015): 17,600 on the islands and 47,300 in the mainland. 

Arrivals continue and during the w/c 29th October 2018, 1,064 people arrived on the islands &#x2013; an increase from 611 arrivals the previous week. Whilst some people are being transferred to the mainland, arrivals on the islands are outpacing departures, increasing the severity of the overcrowding situation on the islands.

EA18/2018 is an eight month EA (01/08/18 &#x2013; 31/03/19) with a focus on protection and improved living conditions for over 12,900 refugees and migrants in Greece as well as vulnerable Greek families. The EA aims to achieve the following specific objectives:

Specific objective 1: Refugees and migrants are facilitated to access public healthcare and psychiatric support
Specific objective 2: Refugees, migrants receive material support in camps to improve their living conditions</narrative>
  </description>
